Gauteng police have confirmed that another body was discovered in the Tladi house in Soweto where a man held his girlfriend hostage on Wednesday.A 37-year-old a man shot and killed himself after holding his partner hostage for more than 12 hours. The injured woman was taken to hospital after her partner released her just before he turned the gun on himself.Forensics arriving at the scene #Tladi hostage bf shot himself dead and a woman rushed to the hospital pic.twitter.com/MNAJoMir7K Thembelihle Mkhonza (@tpmkhonza32) March 8, 2017The hostage situation in #Tladi #Soweto is really concerning @jozifm Zanele Mondi (@ZaneleMondi) March 8, 2017It&#8217;s scary that the end of your life may start by you agreeing to date a guy #tladi THIS IS HOME (@L_Moabelo) March 8, 2017Speaking to Lieutenant Colonel Lungelo Dlamini on Friday, he stated that the body that was discovered was of a 29-year-old man who was a tenant.The motive of the shooting is still unknown and police are yet to release the name of the deceased.The Justice department condemned the kidnapping and shooting of the woman by her partner. This incident is a painful reminder of many women who have perished at the hands of their partners and close relatives, the department said in a statement.This day is meant to affirm the rights of women, we still face the reality of domestic violence and its consequence of intimate femicide which is increasingly becoming a challenge internationally, denying women their inherent dignity and freedoms, the statement read.The department has developed My Safety Plan, to assist victims to escape unharmed and reach for the much needed social and economic support.The Department extends its support to the victim of the incident and implores all citizens to actively promote and affirm the Constitutional rights of all in society.-TNA Reporter 